1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,063
Hello. And welcome to Real Easy English

2
00:00:03,063 --> 00:00:08,079
the podcast where we have real conversations in easy English to help you learn.

3
00:00:08,079 --> 00:00:08,752
I'm Georgie.

4
00:00:08,752 --> 00:00:10,080
And I'm Neil.

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:17,055
Don't forget that there's a video version of this podcast on our website, bbclearningenglish.com.

6
00:00:17,095 --> 00:00:22,015
You can find subtitles to read along and you can download a free worksheet.

7
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:30,970
Hello, Neil.

8
00:00:31,090 --> 00:00:32,150
Hi, Georgie.

9
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:33,190
Happy New Year.

10
00:00:33,190 --> 00:00:33,749
Thank you.

11
00:00:33,749 --> 00:00:35,430
Happy New Year to you too.

12
00:00:35,430 --> 00:00:39,110
Today, we are talking about the start of a new year.

13
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:42,935
So we're going to talk about some of our plans for the new year

14
00:00:42,894 --> 00:00:46,035
and we'll also make some New Year's resolutions.

15
00:00:46,035 --> 00:00:52,214
So this is a tradition where people make promises to themselves for the new year.

16
00:00:52,975 --> 00:00:54,835
They're difficult to keep, aren't they?

17
00:00:54,835 --> 00:00:55,415
They are.

18
00:00:55,870 --> 00:00:57,510
But we try anyway.

19
00:00:57,710 --> 00:00:58,530
Exactly.

20
00:00:58,530 --> 00:01:01,670
So are you excited about the new year, Neil?

21
00:01:01,629 --> 00:01:02,610
I think so.

22
00:01:02,610 --> 00:01:04,069
Twenty twenty six.

23
00:01:04,110 --> 00:01:05,090
Can you believe it?

24
00:01:05,090 --> 00:01:06,450
I cannot believe it.

25
00:01:06,450 --> 00:01:07,170
Okay.

26
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:09,270
So have you got any big plans?

27
00:01:10,185 --> 00:01:15,904
Well, I'm going to start the year with a big trip, actually, with my family.

28
00:01:16,345 --> 00:01:22,365
We're going to South Africa because this is where my parents had their honeymoon

29
00:01:22,365 --> 00:01:25,105
and my mom also used to live there for a while.

30
00:01:25,510 --> 00:01:32,990
So it's a dream of hers to go with the whole family and she can show us around a bit.

31
00:01:33,030 --> 00:01:34,270
What about you?

32
00:01:34,470 --> 00:01:43,355
Well, I don't have any big plans yet, but it's an important year at school, especially for my daughter.

33
00:01:43,955 --> 00:01:48,634
And so when she finishes that her school year

34
00:01:48,675 --> 00:01:54,155
and her exams, maybe we'll do something special to mark that occasion.

35
00:01:54,350 --> 00:02:00,389
So Georgie, it's impossible to talk about the New Year without mentioning resolutions.

36
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:02,709
So what are your resolutions?

37
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:07,910
I think my main one is to make fewer resolutions

38
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:11,255
because last year I made too many

39
00:02:11,215 --> 00:02:14,275
and it was really hard to keep them

40
00:02:14,275 --> 00:02:17,734
and it made me feel very bad about myself.

41
00:02:17,855 --> 00:02:21,495
So this year, I'm just going to keep it simple.

42
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,310
Health, so running.

43
00:02:24,830 --> 00:02:30,209
And language learning, Spanish, I need to do that.

44
00:02:30,209 --> 00:02:34,230
But for running, I think this time I need a big goal.

45
00:02:34,405 --> 00:02:37,305
So I'm a bit scared about it,

46
00:02:37,305 --> 00:02:40,924
but I think I'm going to book a half marathon

47
00:02:41,605 --> 00:02:47,644
because then I can make a training program and feel really motivated.

48
00:02:48,290 --> 00:02:50,010
I think that's what I need.

49
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:51,670
I think that's a great idea.

50
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:54,230
What about you, Neil?

51
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:55,850
Any New Year's resolutions?

52
00:02:56,050 --> 00:03:01,209
Well, usually, once Christmas and New Year are over,

53
00:03:02,025 --> 00:03:10,285
we have the two darkest, saddest months of the year, January and February.

54
00:03:10,285 --> 00:03:17,260
And normally, I really just wish that those months go away and that we get into spring.

55
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:22,960
But this year, I think I'm going to enjoy every day regardless,

56
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,580
you know, even if the weather is awful

57
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:29,334
and it's dark and cold, I still wanna get out there

58
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:33,195
and appreciate it rather than wish my life away.

59
00:03:33,475 --> 00:03:36,614
So Neil, do you have any goals for this year?

60
00:03:36,614 --> 00:03:38,475
So something you want to achieve?

61
00:03:40,195 --> 00:03:45,130
I think I don't really want to take up something new.

62
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:48,489
Take up means start a new activity.

63
00:03:49,330 --> 00:03:56,535
But I think my goal is to become good at something I like doing.

64
00:03:56,535 --> 00:03:57,435
Right.

65
00:03:57,555 --> 00:03:59,495
And what could that be?

66
00:03:59,495 --> 00:04:03,895
So I like learning Spanish Mhmm.

67
00:04:03,895 --> 00:04:05,415
But I'm not very good.

68
00:04:05,415 --> 00:04:06,715
I'm not very dedicated.

69
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:11,479
And I'm always jealous of people who can speak really well.

70
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:15,320
And the same with my guitar.

71
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,240
I always wanna get better.

72
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:22,280
A goal could be to write a song and produce it.

73
00:04:23,215 --> 00:04:25,335
And play it on this podcast.

74
00:04:26,094 --> 00:04:28,275
All really unlucky.

75
00:04:28,275 --> 00:04:30,454
I don't think anyone wants that.

76
00:04:30,974 --> 00:04:32,295
Thank you for your honesty.

77
00:04:40,570 --> 00:04:41,390
Right.

78
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:45,090
Let's recap the language we heard during the conversation.

79
00:04:45,049 --> 00:04:55,704
We heard New Year's resolution, which is a promise you make to yourself at the start of a year to start doing something good or stop doing something bad.

80
00:04:56,705 --> 00:04:58,485
We heard goals.

81
00:04:58,485 --> 00:05:03,704
Now, goals are things that we say that we want to do and try to achieve them.

82
00:05:04,065 --> 00:05:10,490
We also heard motivated, which is a feeling of really wanting to do something and doing it.

83
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:14,970
For example, I feel motivated to run a half marathon this year.

84
00:05:14,929 --> 00:05:18,570
And we heard the expression to wish your life away.

85
00:05:18,765 --> 00:05:24,305
If you wish your life away, you don't appreciate what's happening now.

86
00:05:24,305 --> 00:05:26,085
You look far into the future.

87
00:05:26,445 --> 00:05:29,905
That's it for this episode of Real Easy English.

88
00:05:29,905 --> 00:05:31,845
Do you have a New Year's resolution?

89
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:33,900
We'd love to hear about it.

90
00:05:33,859 --> 00:05:38,940
Email us at learningenglish@bbc.co.uk.

91
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:43,099
Is one of your New Year's resolutions to improve your English?

92
00:05:43,299 --> 00:05:51,575
If so, go to our bbclearningenglish.com, where you can find all kinds of activities and quizzes to help you improve.

93
00:05:51,695 --> 00:05:52,915
Goodbye for now.

94
00:05:52,915 --> 00:05:53,475
Goodbye.
